Feature: Managing Checkpoints

This feature is designed to test the main possible, but basic operations a user can perform
in order to manage checkpoints. Some fundamental connections/ assignments with other CDB objects
might also be tested. Further possible connections/ assignments are tested in the respective feature.

Background:
    Given a project exists
    Given a checklist exists


Scenario Outline: Create New Checkpoint
    When <role> creates a new checkpoint
    Then a new checkpoint is <creation>

    Examples:
        | role            | creation  |
        | Projektmitglied | generated |


Scenario Outline: Change Checkpoint
    Given a checkpoint exists
    When <role> changes this checkpoint
    Then this changed checkpoint is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status |
        | Projektmitglied | saved  |


Scenario Outline: Copy Checkpoint
    Given a checkpoint exists
    When <role> copies this checkpoint
    Then the checkpoint is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status |
        | Projektmitglied | copied |


Scenario Outline: Delete Checkpoint
    Given a checkpoint exists
    When <role> deletes this checkpoint
    Then the checkpoint is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status      |
        | Projektleiter   | deleted     |
        | Projektmitglied | not deleted |


